-- South Korean, U.S. Defense Chiefs Discuss North Korea Since Death of Kim
-- B y   S h i n h y e   K a n g
-- 2011-12-30T02:22:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-30/north-korea-s-succession-is-stable-south-korea-u-s-defense-chiefs-say.html
(Corrects to show defense chiefs stressed importance of
stability on Korean peninsula. Removes incorrect reference to
assessment of succession.)  The defense chiefs of  South Korea 
and the U.S. talked over the telephone to discuss the situation
after the death of Kim Jong Il and stressed the importance of
peace and stability on the Korean peninsula, Kim Min Seok, a
spokesman at the defense ministry in Seoul, told reporters
today. South Korean Defense Minister Kim Kwan Jin and U.S.
Defense Secretary Leon Panetta agreed to closely monitor the
situation in  North Korea , Kim said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shinhye Kang in Seoul at 
 skang24@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Brett Miller at 
 bmiller30@bloomberg.net  